BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hF-D0lNRQ1DwUN6ryP9PD
SUMMARY:Mindfulness Walk | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260307T235610Z
DTSTART:20260319T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Mindfulness Walk\n\nTaking inspiration from the Japanese idea  
	of shinrin-yoku \\(forest bathing\\)\, we will be hosting a series of mind
	fulness walks in Pioneer Park. Mindfulness walking in the forest has shown
	 to  have a myriad of benefits from improving heart health to reducing str
	ess  \\(https://www.npr.org/2023/08/22/1195337204/a-guide-to-forest-bathin
	g\\).\n\n \n\nForest Steward Marilyn Cornwell \\(https://www.soulscapes.us
	/\\) will be lea ding an hour-long guided walk through the park. Please jo
	in us if your cur ious about mindfulness\, want to learn more about and ex
	perience healing powers of being in nature\, and/or if you want to deepen 
	your connection with Pioneer Park and others.\n\nWhen:  Thursday\, March 1
	9th\, 11am-12pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park NW\, Meet at the corner of Island C
	rest Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNTEER EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dr
	ess for the weather in  clothes and shoes you will comfortable walking and
	 standing in\, as well as water. \n\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup
	.org/9XTJA\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mindfulness-wa
	lk-pioneer-park/18066425/2026-03-19T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoor
	s
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mindfulness-walk-pioneer-
	park/18066425/2026-03-19T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
